          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Hebrew/Italian</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>בש"ה</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <list type="ordered">
                                                  <head>Addressed on the outside to:</head>
                                                  <item n="1">(in Hebrew) To the hands of the
                                                  princes, the wise,<lb/> the exalted, etc, in the
                                                  holy congregation of
                                                  <placeName>Phila-<lb/>delphia</placeName>, God
                                                  bless them all together. May they live<lb/>
                                                  forever and ever.</item>
                                                  <item n="2">(in Italian) To the gentlemen, heads
                                                  of the Israe-<lb/>lite nation and the Grand Rabbi
                                                  in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</item>
                                        </list>
                              </p>
                              <p/>
                              <p>(Hebrew)</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>The eve of Rosh Hashonah 1850?</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Wise and understanding men, sons of
                                        <placeName>Israel</placeName>,<lb/> merciful the sons of the
                                        merciful, that is the gentle-<lb/>men, treasurers, the
                                        princes of the community who<lb/> are in the congregation of
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, also the
                                        ex-<lb/>alted wise men who pursue righteousness and<lb/>
                                        kindness, and, at their head, the great and learned</p>
                              <p>* May God grant them everlasting life.<lb/> Peace and life to you,
                                        I direct my prayer that<lb/> God may extend to you many days
                                        and years of<lb/> life, wealth, and the glory of children,
                                        and every<lb/> thing that is good, amen. A year ago I
                                        sent<lb/> you a letter and a new book, and I begged of
                                        you,<lb/> that the righteous ones among you send a gift</p>
                              <p>* The name is omitted and a space left for it. This was<lb/>
                                        evidently a circular letter but the writer did not<lb/> know
                                        the name of the rabbi of the town.</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>to us. Because of two great fires which<lb/> took place in our
                                        town, <placeName>Ismir</placeName>, we are lack-<lb/>ing in
                                        everything. We have become very poor,<lb/> and, especially
                                        I, suffered great losses. Five<lb/> big houses which were
                                        used for houses of study,<lb/> all of them filled with
                                        books, were all burned<lb/> down, even the clothing and
                                        furniture, Also the<lb/> dowry of two grown up daughters was
                                        burnt,<lb/> and it is necessary to make everything all<lb/>
                                        over again. Because of all this, I beg and<lb/> implore that
                                        you, Children of <placeName>Israel</placeName>, have
                                        pity<lb/> upon me, and, because of this, you will all
                                        earn<lb/> life and children, and children's children,<lb/>
                                        with great wealth and honor and strength<lb/> and peace.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <persName role="author">Hayyim Malaggi, Rabbi</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p><placeName>Ismir</placeName> is somewhere near
                                                  <placeName>Salonica</placeName></p>
